The paper deals with the design and analysis of a fully-distributed self-healing algorithm for maintaining a constant degree expander network in a dynamic setting. The algorithm has applications in distributed hash tables and self-healing networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves network protocols and communication algorithms, which fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The algorithm involves maintaining a network topology, which is a fundamental problem in computer science, and hence it can be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the analysis of the algorithm's performance, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
